description: The index into the event list.

the agent can send the Index in Notifications.

description: A Number which uniquely identify a log3 Component.
The Numbers are assigned by log3 number authority
at FSC.

description: A string which describes the module, which send
log3 informations.
One module may have more then one object.
E.g. spool module may have objects printer1
and printer2.

description: A string which describe the modules object, which send
log3 informations.
E.g. printer1.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventObjectID

description: A integer which describes the error code.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventErrorNumber

description: A integer which describes the components error priority.
Components should use syslog(3) priority.
Compoments which use illegal priorities above debug(8) are mapped
to other(9).
A components error priority maybe FATAL, but this does not
implies that the error is FATAL for the system.

description: The system OS process ID.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventProcessId

description: Event reporting system name.

the system, where the events occurred.

description: Time, where event first occurred.

objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3InformationalNotice FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventIndex u 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventComponentNumber u 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventModuleName s EXAMPLE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventObjectID s EXAMPLE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventErrorNumber u 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventErrorWeight i 1 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventProcessId u 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventReleaseVersion s EXAMPLE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventSystemName s EXAMPLE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventNodeName s EXAMPLE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventFirstTime s EXAMPLEE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventSequence c 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventRepeats c 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventLastTime s EXAMPLEE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventUserID u 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventUserName s EXAMPLE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventGroupID u 9999 FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventGroupName s EXAMPLE FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventMessageText s EXAMPLE

description: The index into the event list.
MAX-ACCESS is not set to not-accessible, that
the agent can send the Index in Notifications.
This maybe helpfull for SNMP managers.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventIndex

description: A Number which uniquely identify a log3 Component.
The Numbers are assigned by log3 number authority
at FSC.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventComponentNumber

description: A string which describes the module, which send
log3 informations.
One module may have more then one object.
E.g. spool module may have objects printer1
and printer2.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventModuleName

description: A string which describe the modules object, which send
log3 informations.
E.g. printer1.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventObjectID

description: A integer which describes the error code.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventErrorNumber

description: A integer which describes the components error priority.
Components should use syslog(3) priority.
Compoments which use illegal priorities above debug(8) are mapped
to other(9).
A components error priority maybe FATAL, but this does not
implies that the error is FATAL for the system.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventErrorWeight

description: The system OS process ID.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventProcessId

description: Components release and version number.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventReleaseVersion

description: Event reporting system name.
If a system reports log3 events to a other system
which collect all log3 events, this is the name of
the system, where the events occurred.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventSystemName

description: log3 reporting system name.
If a system reports log3 events to a other system
which collect all log3 events, this is the name of
the system, which collect events from other systems.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventNodeName

description: Time, where event first occurred.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventFirstTime

description: a log3 internal sequence number.
This number could be used to find the sequence of events
if more then one events happens in one second.
log3 is responsible to hold this counter consistent.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventSequence

description: If a event keep going and no other event happens meanwhile
the event will be counted.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventRepeats

description: Time, where event last occurred.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventLastTime

description: The host OS UserID.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventUserID

description: The user who log the event.
This is the UserID, decoded by the host OS.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventUserName

description: The host OS GroupID.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventGroupID

description: The group, where the user belong to.
This is the log3GroupID, decoded by the host OS.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventGroupName

description: This is the message, which the component will log.
This message describe in detail what was happen. The component
is responsible for the text content.
variables.name: FSC-LOG3-MIB::log3EventMessageText
